The following is for everyone that complains about there being too many leechers and not enough seeders.

I always commit to the 1:1 ration as a minimum, if not more. So, in retrospect, I'm always giving back just as much as I took but it's a hard thing to do when there are users like myself that don't have the pleasure of unlimited bandwidth. I'm a Canadian resident and unfortunately, unlimited usage allowances have died off over time so every kilobyte that I seed for everyone is very precious as opposed to those blessed with unlimited upload and download allowances.

I understand that it's no excuse to not be willing to give back what you took (1:1) but that may be a contributing factor for users choosing to not upload as much as they download.
